%N A242569 a(n) = n! - 2*n.
%C A242569 For n > 2, a(n) is the largest value of k such that (n!+k)/(n+k) is an integer.
%C A242569 For n > 2, a(n) is the largest value of k such that (n!+k)/(n+k) is prime.
%C A242569 For n > 1, a(n) is even.
%F A242569 E.g.f.: 1/(1 - x) - 2*x*exp(x). - _Stefano Spezia_, Sep 24 2025
%e A242569 3! - 2*3 = 0 so a(3) = 0.
%e A242569 4! - 2*4 = 16 so a(4) = 16.
%e A242569 5! - 2*5 = 110 so a(5) = 110.
